content:
Enable users to delete one or more sObject records by using the Delete Action. Use an Object's Record Id to determine which record to delete. Vlocity recommends using a merge field in the Path to Id field that refers to an Id or a list of Ids in the data JSON.

Preview the OmniScript and identify the JSON path for the record. For example, this data JSON contains a list of Accounts:
{ "Account":  { "accId": ["001f400000EPQ8o", "001f400000BAkbn"] } }

In the Delete Action properties, click Add sObject to Delete.
Select an Object and enter the JSON path for the record id using merge field syntax.

Preview the OmniScript and use a test record's id to test the functionality.

This page contains information on Delete Action Properties. 

Process arrays using Loop Blocks
Handle errors using Try-Catch Blocks
title: OmniStudio Delete Action
